post_text:
8th Grade Graduation will begin this evening, June 27th. at 7:00 p.m. Please limit the number of guests attending. If you fall into the high risk category, please do not attend for your own safety.

For all who do attend:

1. Please follow CDC guidelines.
2. Families sit together as groups.
3. Groups sit 6 feet apart.
4. Masks are recommended.

Following the guidelines above will allow us to have a traditional graduation ceremony while practicing social distancing. Although we would like everyone to enjoy the graduation experience, we are asking that everyone leave campus immediately after the graduation.

Thank you,
Twylah Morris, Superintendent

The 21st Century after school and summer program will continue in its current digital format through Facebook groups until the end of June. post_text:
ATTENTION PARENTS

The after school and summer program will continue digitally through Facebook groups from May 11-June 30. Teachers will be in contact with parents of students who have enrolled for summer program. They will invite you to join their page where they will offer learning and enrichment opportunities in a digital format. This is an effort to help keep students engaged as well as help prevent loss of knowledge during this long time period out of school. We still plan to try and have an on site summer program, but it may be in July. This is our plan of action for now. We will keep you updated if there are any changes. Please feel free to contact me with any questions or if there is anything I can help you with.
Susan Geer

FYI

Although the Governor is beginning to "open up the state," schools are not included. Only the State School Board can reopen school campuses. They met yesterday and did NOT reopen campuses. This includes little league and any other non-school groups. Unless there is a special State School Board meeting, the next meeting will be on May 28, 2020. With this in mind, we are looking at the June 26 Graduation date for our seniors.

We will try to keep you updated.

Graduation update:

The graduation ceremony is currently scheduled for May 15, 2020 at 7:00 p.m. at the football field.

However, if the social distancing guidelines are not lifted by then, in order to hold a traditional ceremony, the date will be changed to June 26, 2020 at 7:00 p.m. at the football field.

If guidelines still have not been lifted and that date does not work, we are looking at July 10, 2020 at 7:00 p.m. at the football field.

Baccalaureate will be held at 6:00 p.m. in the high school auditorium on the Sunday immediately preceding graduation.

Keota Public School is making every effort to make this school year special for the graduating class of 2020!

post_text: Important information for 8th graders 2020
text: Important information for 8th graders 2020

post_text:
Parents and guardians,

As we enter this new realm of education, please know that we have many of the same concerns that we are hearing from you. How will this work for my child? As educators, we would much rather have your child on campus, eating in the cafeteria, sitting in the classroom, or playing on the playground. However, our country is facing the first pandemic since 1918 and we are all having to make adjustments, learning as we go.

The administration is preparing a plan that must be approved by the Oklahoma Department of Education. This plan will then be shared with the teachers who will begin preparing information to be shared with students and parents. This is a process and we have until April 6 to work through it. We will make adjustments as we go, with hopes that we will be allowed to return to campus in time for summer school.

Please follow this Facebook page for updated information.

Twylah Morris,
Superintendent

post_text:
Thank you to everyone who called the school this week. The government approved breakfast and lunch to be picked up or delivered at the same time, so we will come to your house once per day, Monday through Thursday. Deliveries will begin on Monday, March 23 and continue through April 5.

Your delivery will be between 9:00 a.m. and 10:30 a.m. Grab n go meals can be picked up at the door of the cafeteria from 9:00 to 11:00. Please be patient with us for the first couple of days until we get everything worked out.

EVERYONE 18 years and under are eligible for meals, including preschool children, as well as anyone with a disability up through age 21.

If you do not receive a delivery by 10:30 a.m., please call the school at 918-966-3950 and we will get meals to you ASAP.

Again, this is new to us and we are asking for your patience as we do our best to make sure that everyone who needs a meal is accommodated.

Thank you,
Mrs. Morris, Superintendent
text:
Thank you to everyone who called the school this week. The government approved breakfast and lunch to be picked up or delivered at the same time, so we will come to your house once per day, Monday through Thursday. Deliveries will begin on Monday, March 23 and continue through April 5.

Your delivery will be between 9:00 a.m. and 10:30 a.m. Grab n go meals can be picked up at the door of the cafeteria from 9:00 to 11:00. Please be patient with us for the first couple of days until we get everything worked out.

EVERYONE 18 years and under are eligible for meals, including preschool children, as well as anyone with a disability up through age 21.

If you do not receive a delivery by 10:30 a.m., please call the school at 918-966-3950 and we will get meals to you ASAP.

Again, this is new to us and we are asking for your patience as we do our best to make sure that everyone who needs a meal is accommodated.

Thank you,
Mrs. Morris, Superintendent

It's official, the State Department of Education has closed all Oklahoma Public Schools until April 6, 2020.

This includes all academics and extra-curricular activities. There will be no ball games or practices during that time. No facility usage for little league teams as well during this time period.

We will have all offices open and meals will be provided beginning Monday, March 23rd. I will give you more information later in the week on the process of providing meals and the meal delivery.

We will be on a conference call with the State Superintendent tomorrow at 2 p.m. and will have more information to share with you at that time.

Thank you,
Mrs. Morris, Superintendent

post_text: Please be advised that in accordance with applicable state regulations, Keota Public School district will be destroying all Special Education records (copies of Individualized Education Programs (IEPs) test reports, progress reports, etc.) of students who withdrew, transferred or graduated prior to June 2014. School districts are required to maintain education records, including eligibility documentation and IEPs, for at least 5 years from the student leaving the LEA to demonstrate fiscal accountability and program compliance with the IDEA requirements. Destruction of these records will begin on or after September 1, 2019. Should you wish to obtain your records, you must contact the office at 918-966-3950 prior to August 31, 2019.

post_text:
Today was the last day of our summer school programs here at Keota Public School. Here is an update of our June accomplishments and a shout-out to all of those involved.

The 21st. Century Program, led by Mrs. Geer, served students in grades Pre K and 4-8 with thirty-seven students attending. The program employed 3 teachers, 2 bus drivers, 2 student workers, 2 VISTA volunteers, and 1 administrator.

The Choctaw Posse Program, led by Mrs. McClary, served students in grades K-3 with 56 students attending. The program employed 7 teachers, 4 Choctaw workers, 2 VISTA volunteers, 2 support staff, and 1 administrator.

The Summer Food Program served breakfast and lunch to a daily average of 103 children in the community ages 1-18 years for 24 total days. That is over 4000 meals served! This program employed 2 cooks and 2 VISTA volunteers.

The school has another 5 VISTA volunteers who are mowing, weed eating, painting, and cleaning. The VISTA program will continue through the month of July, so more to come!

Way to go everyone!

post_text:
Keota Public School is looking for Veterans who have moved into the community so that they can be recognized on November 9th at the High School Auditorium.

If you know anyone, please share this invitation to participate. We need them to contact the school and give us name, branch served, and years served, as well as any pictures they may have of themselves.

Our Veteran's Day Program on November 9th will start with lunch in the cafeteria at 12:45 p.m. and then an assembly in the auditorium at 1:15 p.m. ALL Veterans and their families are invited!

Please share!
